# Project Architecture Overview

The **Dynamic Legal Lexicon** is built using a modern decoupled architecture with a focus on modularity and high-performance data retrieval.

## High-Level Architecture

```mermaid
graph TD
    User((User))
    Admin((Admin))

    subgraph "Frontend (React + Vite)"
        UI[User Interface Components]
        Pages[Page Views]
        Services[API Service Layer]
    end

    subgraph "Backend (Node.js + Express)"
        Routes[Express Routes]
        Middleware[Auth & Logging Middleware]
        Models[Data Models]
        Schedulers[Background Schedulers]
    end

    subgraph "External & Database"
        DB[(PostgreSQL)]
        AI[AI Engine - Groq/Gemini]
    end

    User --> UI
    Admin --> UI
    UI --> Pages
    Pages --> Services
    Services --> Routes
    Routes --> Middleware
    Middleware --> Models
    Models --> DB
    Schedulers --> Models
    UI -- "Direct AI Chat" --> AI
```

## 1. Frontend Layer (Modern React)
- **Framework**: [React](https://react.dev/) using [Vite](https://vitejs.dev/) for ultra-fast development and optimized production builds.
- **State Management**: Distributed state using React Hooks (`useState`, `useEffect`, `useContext`).
- **Layout & Styling**: Advanced **Vanilla CSS** utilizing CSS Variables for consistent, project-wide design tokens (colors, spacing, typography).
- **Architecture**: Specialized Service-Component separation. Components consume API services from a centralized [services/api.js](file:///c:/Users/Harini%20S/Downloads/dynamic-legal-lexicon%20ui/dynamic-legal-lexicon-2/frontend/src/services/api.js) layer.

## 2. Backend Layer (Node.js + Express)
- **Modularity**: The backend follows a **Module-First** approach (e.g., `modules/lexicon`, `modules/auth`). Each module contains its own routes, models, and logic.
- **Data Access**: **Model Layer** abstracts raw SQL queries from the business logic.
- **Background Processes**: Uses `node-cron` for automated tasks like the **Daily Term Rotation**, ensuring data stays fresh without manual intervention.
- **Security**: Stateless authentication using **JWT (JSON Web Tokens)** and **Bcrypt** for password hashing.

## 3. Data Layer (PostgreSQL)
- **Relational Integrity**: Leverages PostgreSQL for complex legal data relationships.
- **Optimized Searching**: Implements custom SQL logic for term relevance and full-text search capabilities.
- **Internal Optimization**: Uses PostgreSQL's internal `ctid` pointers for efficient management of large datasets that lack traditional primary keys (like statutory references).

## 4. AI & Integration
- **LLM Connectivity**: Integrates with Groq/Llama-3/Gemini engines to provide:
    - **SmartTradeAI**: Intelligent legal tutoring and chat.
    - **Dynamic Quiz Generation**: Real-time MCQ creation based on legal definitions.
